## 3. The Element Hierarchy

Every element in the theme falls into a layer. Design top-down:

```
Layer 0 — CANVAS
├── Main_Back (47%)           The display surface
├── Body_Back (19-23%)        The control surface
│
Layer 1 — CONTAINERS
├── Pattern_Default_Back (12%)    Pattern editor rows
├── Pattern_Highlighted_Back (4%) Alternating row highlight
├── ValueBox_Back (1-1.4%)        Input fields
├── Button_Back (0.9-1.2%)        All buttons
├── Selected_Button_Back (0.2-0.4%)  Active tab/toggle
│
Layer 2 — INTERACTIVE
├── Slider                        Knobs, faders, scrollbars
├── Selection_Back                Current selection
├── StandBy_Selection_Back        Unfocused selection
├── VuMeter_Meter                 Level meters
│
Layer 3 — TEXT (see Font Contract)
├── Main_Font
├── Body_Font
├── Strong_Body_Font
├── Button_Font
├── Pattern fonts (7+ types)
│
Layer 4 — DEPTH (see Shading)
├── Knob_Shade
├── Body_Shade
├── Main_Font_Shadow
```

### Pixel Budget Reality

| Element | % of screen | Design implication |
|---|---|---|
| `Main_Back` | 47% | This IS your theme's color |
| `Body_Back` | 19-23% | This is your theme's frame |
| `Pattern_Default_Back` | 12% | Must harmonize with Main_Back |
| `Pattern_Highlighted_Back` | 4% | Subtle shift from Default_Back |
| Everything else combined | ~17% | Accents, details, personality |

**Translation:** If someone squints at your theme, they see `Main_Back`. If they unfocus slightly, they see `Main_Back` + `Body_Back`. The rest is detail work.

