## 4. The Font Contract

**The unbreakable rule: every font must be readable against its background.**

This is not a suggestion. This is the contract. Break it and the theme is unusable.

### Font → Background Pairings

| Font | Sits on top of | Minimum contrast ratio |
|---|---|---|
| `Main_Font` | `Main_Back` | 7:1 (WCAG AAA) |
| `Body_Font` | `Body_Back` | 4.5:1 (WCAG AA) |
| `Strong_Body_Font` | `Body_Back` | 7:1 (should pop) |
| `Button_Font` | `Button_Back` | 4.5:1 |
| `Selected_Button_Font` | `Selected_Button_Back` | 4.5:1 |
| `ValueBox_Font` | `ValueBox_Back` | 7:1 (data entry!) |
| `Pattern_Default_Font_*` | `Pattern_Default_Back` | 4.5:1+ |
| `Pattern_Highlighted_Font_*` | `Pattern_Highlighted_Back` | 4.5:1+ |

### The Font Shadow Escape Hatch

`Main_Font_Shadow` can rescue low-contrast fonts by adding a dark halo. But don't rely on it — it only works on `Main_Font`, and it muddies the look if overused.

**Best practice:** Design fonts to be readable WITHOUT shadow first. Add shadow only for polish.

### The Pattern Font Family

The pattern editor has its own micro-typography system:

```
Pattern_Default_Font_Note      — C-4, D#5  (the notes — most important!)
Pattern_Default_Font_Volume    — 40, 7F    (velocity values)
Pattern_Default_Font_Panning   — 80, L20   (stereo position)
Pattern_Default_Font_Pitch     — 01, 0F    (pitch commands)
Pattern_Default_Font_Delay     — Qx        (timing)
Pattern_Default_Font_Global    — ZT, ZL    (global FX)
Pattern_Default_Font_Unused    — .. --     (empty cells)
```

Each has a `Highlighted` variant for alternating rows.

**Design principle:** The **note column is king**. It should be the most readable, the most contrasty. Volume and panning can be slightly muted. Unused cells (the `..` dots) should **recede** — they're visual noise.

A common pro technique:
```
Note:    full brightness white/color
Volume:  80% brightness
Panning: 60% brightness
Unused:  30% brightness (barely visible)
```

This creates a natural visual hierarchy where your eye finds the notes instantly.

