## 5. Color Decision Chains

Don't pick colors randomly. Each choice constrains the next.

### Chain 1: The Background Chain

```
START
  │
  ▼
Pick Main_Back ──────────────────────── This is THE color. Dark? Light? Tinted?
  │
  ▼
Pick Body_Back ──────────────────────── What's the relationship? (See Section 2)
  │
  ├──▶ Pattern_Default_Back            Usually = Main_Back or very close
  │      │
  │      └──▶ Pattern_Highlighted_Back Shift lightness by 5-15% from Default
  │
  ├──▶ ValueBox_Back                   Darker than Body_Back (recessed input fields)
  │
  └──▶ Button_Back                     Between Body_Back and Main_Back, or an accent
```

### Chain 2: The Font Chain

```
After backgrounds are set:
  │
  ▼
Pick Main_Font ──────────────────────── Must contrast Main_Back. Usually light.
  │
  ▼
Pick Body_Font ──────────────────────── Must contrast Body_Back. Can match Main_Font or differ.
  │
  ├──▶ Strong_Body_Font               Brighter/bolder Body_Font
  │
  ├──▶ Button_Font                     Must contrast Button_Back
  │
  └──▶ All Pattern fonts               Must contrast Pattern_Default_Back AND Pattern_Highlighted_Back
```

### Chain 3: The Accent Chain

```
After backgrounds + fonts:
  │
  ▼
Pick Selection_Back ─────────────────── THE accent color. Blue? Orange? Theme's signature.
  │
  ├──▶ StandBy_Selection_Back          Desaturated version (30-50% saturation)
  │
  ├──▶ Selected_Button_Back            Can match or complement Selection_Back
  │
  ├──▶ VuMeter_Meter                   Usually green for "signal" or matches accent
  │
  └──▶ Slider                          Can match accent or stay neutral
```

### Chain 4: The Depth Chain

```
After all colors:
  │
  ▼
Derive shading from existing colors (see Section 6)
```

