## 6. Shading & Texture: The Anti-Flat Toolkit

Renoise provides shading elements that add dimensionality. Most theme designers ignore these. Don't.

### Body_Shade

A gradient/overlay color applied to `Body_Back` areas.

```
Body_Back:  #3A3A4A (the base)
Body_Shade: #00000033 (semi-transparent black)
```

**Effect:** Panels get subtle top-to-bottom gradient. Feels like light hitting a physical surface.

**Rules:**
- Use a semi-transparent dark color for a "lit from above" look
- Use a semi-transparent light color for a "glowing" look
- Use `#00000000` (fully transparent) for dead flat
- **Subtle is better** — opacity between 10-30% (hex `1A`-`4D` in alpha channel)

### Knob_Shade

Applied to knobs, sliders controls.

```
Slider:     #6688AA (the knob color)
Knob_Shade: #FFFFFF20 (slight white sheen)
```

**Effect:** Knobs appear to have a specular highlight, like polished plastic.

**Techniques:**
- White shade = glossy plastic knob
- Black shade = matte rubber knob
- Colored shade = metallic / anodized aluminum
- No shade = flat UI / digital feel

### Main_Font_Shadow

A drop shadow behind Main_Font text.

```
Main_Font:        #FFFFFF (white text)
Main_Font_Shadow: #000000AA (dark shadow behind it)
```

**Use when:**
- Main_Back has texture or variation
- You want an "LED display" glow (use colored shadow matching font)
- Font contrast is borderline (shadow rescues it)

**Skip when:**
- Theme is flat/modern
- Main_Back is very dark already (shadow is invisible / adds mud)

### Shadow + Shade Recipes

| Look | Body_Shade | Knob_Shade | Font_Shadow |
|---|---|---|---|
| Hardware synth | `#00000030` | `#FFFFFF18` | `#000000AA` |
| Flat modern | `#00000000` | `#00000000` | `#00000000` |
| Neon/cyberpunk | `#00000050` | accent color `40` | accent color `88` |
| Vintage/warm | `#0000001A` | `#FFFFFF10` | `#00000060` |
| Glass/frost | `#FFFFFF10` | `#FFFFFF30` | `#00000040` |

