## 9. Design Archetypes

### The Workhorse

> For 12-hour sessions. Nothing should tire the eyes.

```
Main_Back:           very dark, neutral (#161620)
Body_Back:           slightly lighter (#252530)
Main_Font:           off-white (#C8C8D0) — NOT pure white
Body_Font:           grey (#888898)
Selection_Back:      muted blue (#2A4060)
Pattern fonts:       low saturation, good contrast
Shading:             minimal
```

**Key principle:** No pure whites, no vivid colors, no high saturation. Everything muted. The music is the star, not the UI.

### The Showpiece

> For screenshots. Maximum beauty.

```
Main_Back:           deep color-tinted (#0A0A1A navy)
Body_Back:           complementary tint (#1A1210 warm brown)
Selection_Back:      vivid accent (#FF6B35 orange)
Pattern fonts:       color-coded, saturated
Shading:             rich, use all shade elements
VuMeter:             neon or vivid
```

**Key principle:** This theme tells a story. Every color is intentional. It photographs well. It might tire the eyes after 4 hours, and that's OK.

### The Flat/Modern

> Clean lines, no skeuomorphism.

```
Main_Back:           pure dark (#1A1A1A)
Body_Back:           one step up (#242424)
All fonts:           one color, two brightnesses
Selection_Back:      single accent hue
Shading:             ALL transparent (flat)
Button_Back:         barely different from Body_Back
```

**Key principle:** Reduction. Every element that can be the same, should be. The theme disappears. Content reigns.

### The Neon/Cyberpunk

> Blade Runner's music studio.

```
Main_Back:           near-black (#08080C)
Body_Back:           dark with color (#0E1420 blue-dark)
Main_Font:           neon color (#00FFAA)
Selection_Back:      hot pink (#FF0066)
Font_Shadow:         matching neon glow (#00FFAA44)
VuMeter:             vivid green or matching neon
Shading:             dark, heavy depth
```

**Key principle:** Dark backgrounds make neon colors glow. Use font shadow as "LED glow". High contrast, high saturation — against near-black.

### The Vintage/Warm

> Analog vibes. Tape machine. Warm studio.

```
Main_Back:           warm dark (#1A1410)
Body_Back:           warm medium (#2E2820)
Main_Font:           amber (#CCAA77)
Pattern fonts:       earth tones, amber, cream
Selection_Back:      warm accent (#885522)
Knob_Shade:          warm white (#FFEECC18)
```

**Key principle:** No blue, no cool tones. Everything through an amber filter. Like the theme is lit by incandescent bulbs.

### The Light Theme (Rare, Risky)

> For daylight working. Very few succeed.

```
Main_Back:           off-white (#EEEEF0)
Body_Back:           light grey (#D8D8DC)
Main_Font:           near-black (#1A1A2E)
Pattern_Default_Back: white (#F4F4F8)
Selection_Back:      medium blue (#4488CC)
```

**Key principle:** WCAG contrast is critical. Light themes expose every contrast mistake. Test ruthlessly. Most Renoise users will hate it instinctively — make it exceptionally functional or don't bother.

