## 10. Contrast Math

### WCAG Relative Luminance

For any color `#RRGGBB`:

$$L = 0.2126 \times R_s + 0.7152 \times G_s + 0.0722 \times B_s$$

where $R_s$, $G_s$, $B_s$ are the sRGB values linearized:

$$C_s = \begin{cases} C/12.92 & \text{if } C \leq 0.04045 \\ \left(\frac{C + 0.055}{1.055}\right)^{2.4} & \text{otherwise} \end{cases}$$

### Contrast Ratio

$$CR = \frac{L_{\text{lighter}} + 0.05}{L_{\text{darker}} + 0.05}$$

### Required Ratios

| Use case | Minimum CR | Target CR |
|---|---|---|
| Body text (fonts on backgrounds) | 4.5:1 (AA) | 7:1 (AAA) |
| Large text / headings | 3:1 | 4.5:1 |
| Pattern note column | 7:1+ | As high as possible |
| Pattern unused cells | 1.5:1 minimum | 2-3:1 (intentionally low) |
| UI borders / separators | 3:1 | — |
| Selection_Back vs row background | 3:1+ | Obvious at a glance |

### Quick Contrast Checks (Dark Theme)

For a dark theme with `Main_Back: #161620`:

| Font Color | Approx CR | Verdict |
|---|---|---|
| `#FFFFFF` | 16:1 | ✅ Excellent but harsh |
| `#C8C8D0` | 11:1 | ✅ Perfect for long sessions |
| `#888898` | 4.8:1 | ✅ Good for secondary text |
| `#555566` | 2.5:1 | ⚠️ Only for unused/decorative |
| `#333344` | 1.5:1 | ⚠️ Nearly invisible (good for Unused font) |
| `#222230` | 1.1:1 | ❌ Invisible |

