## 12. Color Picking Order

The recommended sequence for designing a theme from scratch:

```
Step 1:  INTENTION
         What is this theme for? Work / Show / Experiment?
         Light or dark? Warm or cool? Flat or textured?

Step 2:  MAIN_BACK
         The canvas. 47% of your theme. Go dark, go subtle.

Step 3:  BODY_BACK
         The frame. Decide the relationship to Main_Back (Section 2).

Step 4:  MAIN_FONT + BODY_FONT
         Contrast check. If these fail, nothing else matters.

Step 5:  PATTERN_DEFAULT_BACK + PATTERN_HIGHLIGHTED_BACK
         Usually derived from Main_Back. Define the pattern editor foundation.

Step 6:  PATTERN FONTS (all 7 types × 2 row variants = 14 colors)
         The biggest color commitment. Build the hierarchy (Section 8).
         Test on both Default_Back and Highlighted_Back.

Step 7:  SELECTION_BACK
         The accent. Your theme's personality color.
         Check: is it visible on both Pattern backs?

Step 8:  STANDBY_SELECTION_BACK
         Muted version of Selection. Don't skip this.

Step 9:  BUTTON_BACK + SELECTED_BUTTON_BACK + FONTS
         The control layer. Derived from Body_Back.

Step 10: VALUEBOX_BACK + FONT
         Input fields. Usually darker than Body_Back (recessed).

Step 11: SLIDER + VUEMETER
         Interactive elements. Match or complement the accent.

Step 12: CURSOR + PATTERN_CENTERBAR_BACK
         Navigation indicators. Test in the pattern editor.

Step 13: SHADING (Body_Shade, Knob_Shade, Main_Font_Shadow)
         The polish layer. Add depth. Test with and without.

Step 14: EDGE CASES
         StandBy fonts, Selected_Button_Font, Strong_Body_Font.
         These are easy to forget and create jarring moments.

Step 15: FULL PREVIEW
         Render all three views (pattern, mixer, waveform).
         Look at them at thumbnail size. Squint. Does it feel right?
```

